<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOING WITH THE FLOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mentally tough athletes not only view stress as a challenge but also thrive on 
successfully overcoming pressure ("Comeback Man," by Pat Jordan, Feb. 13). The 
comeback attempts of previous Olympic stars Brian Boitano and Katarina Witt -- 
like Michael Jordan's flirtation with a career as a major-league baseball 
player -- are testimony that top performers revel in the "flow" of a peak 
performance and often try to create new challenges for themselves. 
</P>
<P>
 CLARENCE B. SANTOS 
</P>
<P>
 Adelanto 
</P>
