<TEXT>
<P>
 ZAP!: How Your Computer Can Hurt You -- And What You Can Do About It by Don 
Sellers (Peachpit Press: $12.95; 150 pp., illustrated, paperback original). The 
Bureau of Labor Statistics estimates that 4.4 million Americans suffer from 
computer-related CTD's (cumulative trauma disorders). Sellers examines some of 
the causes of these problems and offers solutions that range from reducing 
stress to installing ergonomic work stations. Although an interesting overview, 
"Zap!" is hardly the definitive book on the subject. The chapter on glasses 
omits the radiation-blocking properties of some plastic lenses; the discussion 
of lighting mentions problems associated with fluorescent tubes, but fails to 
assess the merits of incandescent and halogen bulbs. 
</P>
