<P>
 GET YOUR TONGUE OUT OF MY MOUTH, I'M KISSING YOU GOOD-BYE! by Cynthia Heimel 
(Fawcett: $10; 179 pp.). Heimel offers her waspishly funny comments on life, 
love and feminism in this collection of essays.Many of these subjects have been 
covered by other writers -- love in the '90s, the search for commitment as men 
and women vie for the title of victim, New York vs. Los Angeles. What sets 
