<HEADLINE>
<P>
PALM LATITUDES: L.A. SPEAK; FLIGHT ATTENDANTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Laura A. Galloway 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 bag drag: n . when a flight attendant takes a trip but never even opens her 
luggage. 
</P>
<P>
 cockpit queen: n . a flight attendant who fraternizes with the pilots."I 
couldn't get that cockpit queen to help me with the cart." 
</P>
<P>
 death trap: n . an unpleasant route. "If you can avoid it, don't get scheduled 
for the L.A. to Rio. It's a real death trap. " 
</P>
<P>
 fruit and nut run: n. a flight to Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 sell one's soul: working more than an 18-hour shift. "I needed the money, so I 
sold my soul. " 
</P>
<P>
 tease trip: n . a flight to a desirable location on a schedule that leaves 
little or no time to spend there. "We landed in Bali Tuesday night and had to 
fly back to the States the next morning. It was the biggest tease trip ." 
</P>
<P>
 walking the dog: v. wheeling your bags through an airport. "Walking the dog 
through O'Hare is such a pain. It feels like you're trudging across all of 
Rhode Island!" Laura A. Galloway 
</P>
</TEXT>
