<HEADLINE>
<P>
STYLE; MEN'S SPRING FASHION; PARALLEL LINES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL EISENHOWER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Menswear designers have long licensed large corporations to produce 
accessories and moderately priced clothing bearing their names.Secondary lines, 
or fashions created by the designers' own in-house teams, are a more recent 
development. 
</P>
<P>
 With more direct input in these alternative lines, designers now bring 
elements of inventive, high-end fashion within reach of a younger, slightly 
less affluent customer. 
</P>
<P>
 Designers' collections will always set the pace, but this spring, secondary 
lines also provide some of the best styles of the season -- loosely woven 
sweaters, drawstring pants, vintage and workwear looks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
