<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP MUSIC CHARTS: THE HOT SOUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It's rare that two albums by hot alternative-rock bands like Soundgarden and 
Nine Inch Nails come out at the same time. But it's allowing alternative to 
dominate The Times' Southern California pop album chart. Still, pop princesses 
Celine Dion and Toni Braxton are so popular either might reclaim the top spot. 
Raunch is ruling the pop singles chart right now, with R. Kelly's sexy "Bump 
'n' Grind" muscling out Dion's wholesome "The Power of Love." TOP 10 ALBUMS 
