<HEADLINE>
<P>
RERUNS TO REWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rob Reiner appears on The Rockford Files (Monday at 10 a.m. on A&E) in an 
episode that finds Jim involved in a blackmail scheme. 
</P>
<P>
 He knows when to hold them. He knows when to fold them. He knows when to walk 
away. He's Kenny Rogers as "The Gambler," and this week at 10:05 a.m. TBS 
presents three of his TV movies. Monday: Kenny Rogers as The Gambler. 
Tuesday-Wednesday: Kenny Rogers as the Gambler, Part II: The Adventure 
Continues. Thursday-Friday: Kenny Rogers as the Gambler, Part III: The Legend 
Continues. 
</P>
<P>
 Lisa Hartman, Bruce Dern and Richard Masur star in Roses Are for the Rich 
(Monday and Tuesday at 10 a.m. on Lifetime), a four-hour 1986 drama about a 
young woman who seeks revenge on the man who destroyed her family. 
</P>
<P>
 Director Garry Marshall ("Pretty Woman") plays a boxing referee on The Dick 
Van Dyke Show (Tuesday at 11 p.m. on Nickelodeon). 
</P>
<P>
 Karl Malden, Eva Marie Saint, Gary Cole and Andy Griffith star in Fatal Vision 
(Wednesday and Thursday at 9 p.m. on Lifetime), the acclaimed 1984 adaptation 
of Joe McGinnis' bestseller about the murder case of former Green Beret Capt. 
Jeffrey MacDonald. 
</P>
<P>
 After an eight-year absence, Elvis Presley returned to TV in the now-legendary 
special Elvis '68 (Wednesday at 10 p.m. on the Disney Channel). 
</P>
<P>
 Check out the early work of Oscar-nominated Tommy Lee Jones of "The Fugitive" 
in two acclaimed miniseries: 1977's The Amazing Howard Hughes (Thursday at 5:50 
p.m. on TBS), followed at 8:05 p.m. by 1982's The Executioner's Song, in which 
Jones plays convicted murderer Gary Gilmore. 
</P>
<P>
 Cloris Leachman makes her last appearance as Phyllis on The Mary Tyler Moore 
Show (Thursday at 10:30 p.m. on Nickelodeon). 
</P>
<P>
 Very Very Nick at Nite (Saturday at 10 p.m. on Nickelodeon) presents "Very 
Very Rhoda," four Rhoda-themed episodes of "The Mary Tyler Moore Show." 
</P>
