<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WORD IS EGO  
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I'm sure it was not Daniel Cerone's fault, but there are many inaccuracies in 
his article "Expatriate Games" (March 6): 
</P>
<P>
 * I did not do any acting in the film "Day of Reckoning," nor was I ever 
interested in doing such. I was the co-creator and co-executive producer of 
this Paramount Studios-NBC movie. 
</P>
<P>
 * The article suggests my partner Stirling Silliphant and I are at "odds" over 
the production, the deal-making and the results of the final product. Nothing 
could be further from the truth. We are actively engaged in developing a new 
television series to be filmed on location in Paris. I never "sold away" our 
rights to the project against Stirling's wishes; as partners, we make all such 
decisions jointly. 
</P>
<P>
 * As for the "name" power of my getting projects financed, the long list of 
past, present and future projects speaks for itself. 
</P>
<P>
 Perhaps a better title for Cerone's article would have been "Ego Games" -- one 
of the very reasons Stirling and I choose to write and produce outside the 
Hollywood system. 
</P>
<P>
 ROBERT GINTY 
</P>
<P>
 Hollywood 
</P>
