<HEADLINE>
<P>
GARDENER'S CHECKLIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen on what to do in the garden this week: 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * The color impact of your garden can be increased by planting containers with 
seasonal annuals as the finishing touch. 
</P>
<P>
 * Celebrate Easter with a flowering plant as a gift to yourself or someone 
special. 
</P>
<P>
 * When the Easter Lily flower begins to fade, plant it outdoors in a 
semi-shade area to bring it back to bloom next year. 
</P>
<P>
 * Sow vegetables such as lettuce, radishes, corn and carrots in successive 
planting to lengthen your harvest time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
