<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; RIPON CHRISTIAN WINS TWO TITLES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ERIC SHEPARD and WENDY WITHERSPOON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ripon Christian High of the Sac-Joaquin Section won a record third State 
Division V boys' basketball title with a 60-46 victory over Pacific Hills 
Saturday at the Oakland Coliseum Arena. 
</P>
<P>
 The Knights (35-1) also won titles in 1988 and '92.Pacific Hills, previously 
known as Bel-Air Prep, also finished as the Division V runner-up in 1989. 
</P>
<P>
 Ripon Christian led from start to finish, building a 33-21 halftime margin. 
Forward Phil Mensonides had 19 points and 10 rebounds for the Knights. 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific Hills (24-9) shot 27% from the field. Forward Danny Brummel led the 
Bruins with 14 points. Forward Bryan Sterling had a game-high 14 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Ripon Christian 62, El Cajon Christian 46 -- Jenny Miller scored 18 points to 
lead the Knights to the State Division V girls' championship. 
</P>
<P>
 Ripon Christian (31-5) went on a 9-0 run in the final 1:25 of the third 
quarter to take a 47-38 lead. The Patriots (28-5) never got closer than seven 
points in the fourth quarter. ERIC SHEPARD and WENDY WITHERSPOON 
</P>
</TEXT>
