<P>
 In the Division I girls' game: 
</P>
<P>
 Atherton Sacred Heart Prep 59, Lynwood 53 -- Sacred Heart, the defending 
Division V champion playing its first season in Division I, completed an 
unbeaten season by knocking off the defending division champions. 
</P>
<P>
 At 38-0, Sacred Heart broke its own record for victories in a season set last 
year, when it was 37-0. 
</P>
<P>
 Alexis Felts scored eight points during a 13-4 run midway through the fourth 
quarter to put the game out of reach. 
</P>
<P>
 Felts, a senior guard, had a game-high 26 points, including 12 of 13 free 
throw attempts. Jennifer Circle, a 6-foot-3 junior center, had 18 points and 
nine rebounds for the Gators. 
</P>
<P>
 Lynwood (32-2) was hindered by early foul trouble. Timicha Kirby, the Knights' 
leading scorer, picked up two fouls in the first quarter. WENDY WITHERSPOON 
