<HEADLINE>
<P>
ABOUT 50 EVENTS POSTPONED BY RAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Katella Relays high school track and field meet and the UCLA-Cal State 
Fullerton baseball game were among about 50 college, community college and high 
school events postponed by rain Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The Katella Relays have been rescheduled for April 9 at 9 a.m., and the 
Titans' meeting with the Bruins was rescheduled for 7 p.m. May 11 at Titan 
Field. 
</P>
<P>
 Three community college baseball games were rained out, with Riverside at 
Cypress and Golden West at Orange Coast being rescheduled for 1 p.m. today. 
</P>
<P>
 All games in the Argo Invitational high school softball tournament were 
postponed, with no make-up day determined. 
</P>
</TEXT>
