 In nonleague baseball: 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach 3-9, Newhall Hart 2-3 -- Jeremy Vidales' seventh-inning 
double tied the first game, then Scott Palmer scored on a passed ball to win it 
for Huntington Beach (7-1). Palmer hit a solo homer in the sixth.In the second 
game, Brad Lineberger hit a three-run homer to lead a 13-hit attack. 
</P>
<P>
 Tustin 1-6, Arroyo Grande 5-5 -- After a three-hour rain delay the teams were 
able to take the field. In the second game, Derek Baker hit a solo home run in 
the fourth inning to bring Tustin (5-3) within one, 3-2. Baker also added a 
double and two RBIs. Matt Trujillo hit a homer in the fifth to give the Tillers 
the lead. Trujillo went two for two in the game. Arroyo Grande is 5-3. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Canyon Relays boys' swimming meet: 
</P>
