<HEADLINE>
<P>
OCC MEN, WOMEN DO WELL AT SWIM MEET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Orange Coast College men's and women's swim teams won Saturday in the 
Wells Invitational at Cuesta College in San Luis Obispo. 
</P>
<P>
 The men's team scored 619 points, winning four of five relays and four 
individual titles -- three by Matthias Otte -- in the second day of competition 
to outdistance second-place Cuesta (515 1/2). Golden West was third with 417 
points. 
</P>
<P>
 Otte won the 100 backstroke, the 100 breaststroke and the 50 freestyle. 
</P>
<P>
 The OCC women scored 756 points, winning three relays and two individual 
titles Saturday. Diablo Valley was second with 332 points and the Golden West 
women were fifth with 261. 
</P>
</TEXT>
