BLAST IN AZERI SUBWAY STATION KILLS AT LEAST 12 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A remote-controlled bomb exploded in a crowded Baku subway station Saturday, 
killing at least 12 people, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The device exploded midafternoon as a train pulled in, witnesses said. It 
ripped off the roof of the first car. 
</P>
<P>
 Azerbaijan has been fighting a six-year war with neighboring Armenia over the 
disputed enclave of Nagorno-Karabakh. It also has been gripped by internal 
political strife, and the government cracked down earlier this month on 
opposition groups. 
