<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: WOMAN KILLED, 5 HURT IN HEAD-ON COLLISION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 24-year-old Oxnard woman died following a head-on collision on a stretch of 
Santa Rosa Road in Camarillo Saturday morning, sheriff's officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Yolanda Aldape died of head and chest injuries at Pleasant Valley Hospital at 
8:47 a.m., officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Five other people were injured in the collision, which occurred on a curve of 
Santa Rosa Road by the Camrosa Water District headquarters. 
</P>
<P>
 The crash occurred shortly after 7 a.m. when Aldape's husband, Fernando 
Jimenez, crossed over the center divider in his small pickup truck and collided 
with a full-size pickup driven by Ramon Garcia of Oxnard, Lt. Gary Backman 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Jimenez and his four adult passengers -- Aldape and another in the cab and two 
in the truck bed -- were all injured. 
</P>
<P>
 Jimenez was taken to St. John's Regional Medical Center with internal injuries 
and was listed in serious condition in the intensive care unit Saturday night, 
a nursing supervisor said. 
</P>
<P>
 Garcia was taken to Pleasant Valley Hospital with moderate injuries. 
</P>
<P>
 He was treated and released, a nursing supervisor said. 
</P>
<P>
 Conditions and injuries of Jimenez's other three passengers were not reported. 
</P>
<P>
 Sheriff's officials said they were unsure whether the accident was caused by 
speeding or rain. 
</P>
<P>
 At least three other people have died in automobile accidents on Santa Rosa 
Road in recent years. TRACY WILSON 
</P>
</TEXT>
