<P>
PHOTO MISLEADING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 On Feb. 23, you published an article about the city of Oxnard's intention to 
file a tax lien on the Oxnard Town Center. I was terribly disappointed to see 
that your paper chose to include photographs of our property, 1000 Town 
Center.This is very misleading. 
</P>
<P>
 Bedford Property Investors recently purchased the building, all cash, and has 
reserved funds up front for any new leasing or capital improvements. All 
property taxes and bond assessments associated with the building are current. 
</P>
<P>
 The article refers to some nearby unimproved land parcels, in which we have no 
interest. Your publication no doubt chose our building to photograph due to its 
prominent appearance and proximity to the strawberry fields, which are the 
subject of the article. Rest assured, Bedford Property Investors has long-term 
plans for 1000 Town Center Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 PETER B. BEDFORD 
