<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHARITIES NOT RELATED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura citizens should read the fine print of all fund-raising appeals before 
making a donation.As president of the American Heart Assn., San Buenaventura 
Division, I am concerned that people are confusing Heart Support of America 
with the American Heart Assn. There is no connection. 
</P>
<P>
 The American Heart Assn. has provided over $1 billion for research since 1924 
and has an audited financial statement. According to Heart Support of America's 
own literature: The group was founded in 1991, has no audited financial 
statement and spends 60% of its contributions on fund-raising. By comparison, 
the American Heart Assn. spends 14% on fund-raising. 
</P>
<P>
 Please make sure your donation goes to the intended agency. 
</P>
<P>
 WILLIAM SPEITEL, M.D. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura 
