<HEADLINE>
<P>
ZIP CODE VEXATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Supervisor Maria VanderKolk expressed regret that she could not give the 
community of Oak Park a new ZIP code, as requested by our community's elected 
leaders ("Annexation Is Urged for Oak Park," March 11). 
</P>
<P>
 I am upset that she never seriously tried to resolve this problem that too 
often causes Oak Park residents to be treated as if they live in Los Angeles 
County. 
</P>
<P>
 Starting the process for a new ZIP code would have been easy. VanderKolk 
merely had to introduce a resolution at a meeting of the Board of Supervisors, 
requesting the Postal Service to begin the process. But despite repeated 
requests from Oak Park residents, VanderKolk never introduced the required 
resolution to the board. 
</P>
<P>
 I just do not understand her position that "They want things, like a new ZIP 
code, that I can't give them." She never really tried. 
</P>
<P>
 DAVID E. ROSS 
