<HEADLINE>
<P>
FORUM PLANNED ON BUSINESS DISTRICTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Community Redevelopment Agency and its community advisory committees will 
host a public forum Wednesday to discuss strategies for revitalizing local 
business districts. 
</P>
<P>
 The forum begins at 7 p.m. at the Broadway Federal Savings & Loan, 4835 W. 
Venice Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 The agency's staff will give updates on conditions in the study areas -- the 
Midtown Shopping Center and portions of Jefferson, Adams, Washington, Venice, 
Pico and Crenshaw boulevards -- and talk about the options being considered to 
boost business and improve the quality of life in the study area. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 766-9830. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA032094-0271 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 024673 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
March 20, 1994, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
