<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: MID-CITY: RECEPTION PLANNED FOR RAMPART POLICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Westlake-Pico Union Community Improvement Council will hold a free 
reception Thursday to welcome new command personnel and patrol officers in the 
Police Department's Rampart Division and to honor officers who have been 
working with the community to improve safety. 
</P>
<P>
 The reception begins at 3 p.m. at the Park Plaza Hotel, 607 S. Park View St., 
and will feature representatives from several city agencies and departments 
offering updates on community services. 
</P>
<P>
 The council is coordinating the efforts of groups in the two neighborhoods and 
wants to share ideas on safety and improving conditions for businesses and 
residents, said organizer Lauren Bryant. 
</P>
<P>
 Reservations are requested: (213) 483-3430 or (213) 413-2666. 
</P>
</TEXT>
