<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: CENTRAL: ECHO PARK; PREGNANT? BILINGUAL NUTRITION LECTURE SET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A free, bilingual lecture on nutrition during pregnancy will be presented 
Saturday at the Echo Park Branch Library, 515 N. Laveta Terrace. 
</P>
<P>
 "Eating for Two" will be presented in English and Spanish by Cecilia Arias of 
CIGNA's Health Education Division.The lecture begins at 1 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 This event is one of a series of free, health-related presentations offered 
through April at library branches in the Northeast region, which includes 
Chinatown, Little Tokyo and East Los Angeles. The lecture at each branch is 
tailored to the community's health concerns and language needs, said Sylvia 
Galan-Garcia, senior librarian at the Echo Park branch. 
</P>
<P>
 Other branches provided information on smoking, diabetes and shiatsu massage, 
but staff at the Echo Park branch saw a need for a pregnancy-related lecture. 
"We get a lot of requests for books on pregnancy and prenatal care," 
Galan-Garcia said. 
</P>
<P>
 The lecture series is being funded by a grant from the American Library Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 250-7808. 
</P>
