COMMUNITY NEWS: CENTRAL: DOWNTOWN; ESSAY, POSTER CONTEST IS OPEN TO STUDENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Students in kindergarten through 12th grade can win scholarships for creating 
a poster or writing an essay on the theme "Celebrating the Family: Foundation 
of Our Future." 
</P>
<P>
 The deadline for the poster and essay contest is April 8.Essays should be a 
maximum of 500 words and posters should be at least 11 by 14 inches and no 
larger than 24 by 35 inches. 
</P>
<P>
 Scholarships of $50 to $300 will be awarded to first- through third-place 
winners in four grade divisions. Winners will be honored at a May 11 reception 
at the Los Angeles Unified School District Board of Education. 
</P>
<P>
 The contest is sponsored by the school district's Asian Pacific American 
Education Commission and the Los Angeles Asian Pacific American Heritage Month 
Committee. 
</P>
