<HEADLINE>
<P>
CLINIC MOVING TO LARGER SITE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Msgr. Oscar Romero Clinic is moving to 1125 West 6th St. to increase the 
number of patients it treats. 
</P>
<P>
 "We need more space to expand our services," said Juan Ruiz, a physician and 
chairman of the clinic's board of directors. 
</P>
<P>
 The clinic, which was established in 1983, has closed at 2675 W. Olympic Blvd. 
It will reopen April 4 at the new address. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 389-0280. 
</P>
</TEXT>
