<P>
DRIVER CHARGED WITH MANSLAUGHTER IN DEATHS OF 12 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Twelve vehicular manslaughter charges were filed against the driver of a 
pickup carrying 20 people that crashed in an irrigation ditch, killing 12 
passengers. 
</P>
<P>
 Wenndever Ordonez, 23, was to be arraigned on the felony charges this week, 
Deputy Dist. Atty. Steve Sinfeld said. 
</P>
<P>
 Ordonez was driving a compact pickup south of Barstow on Interstate 15 when it 
crashed in the ditch March 9. The truck was crammed with passengers who 
apparently entered the United States illegally. 
</P>
<P>
 The manslaughter charges were filed Friday. Also filed were misdemeanor 
charges of being an unlicensed driver, having a fraudulent driver's license, 
making an unsafe turning movement and not wearing a seat belt. 
</P>
