<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA ANA MAN FATALLY SHOT WHEN 'FLYER PARTY' IS CRASHED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 19-year-old man was fatally wounded after several men described as gang 
members opened fire in a crowded party Friday night, authorities said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 George John Rodriguez of Santa Ana was shot several times at the party in a 
home in the 1600 block of South Halladay Street, Santa Ana police said.Friends 
drove him to Coastal Communities Hospital, where he was pronounced dead about 
10:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Two "party crews," groups of friends who put on parties often advertised by 
leaflets, had organized the party Friday night. At about 10:10 p.m., Sgt. Dan 
Carr said, several gang members crashed the party, where 30 to 50 people were 
in attendance. 
</P>
<P>
 When organizers asked the alleged gang members to leave, the young men fired 
several shots, Carr said. Police found Rodriguez, a party guest, with multiple 
gunshot wounds. No arrests were made and no weapons were recovered, police 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
