<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 SHOT BY INTRUDER IN BOTCHED COMPUTER THEFT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two Reseda men were shot and critically wounded Saturday by an armed intruder 
who pretended to be interested in buying a computer that one of the men had 
recently listed in the Recycler, a weekly advertiser, Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
 A man in his early 20s knocked on the door of a house in the 18400 block of 
Keswick Street about 6 p.m. and inquired about the computer.Once inside, the 
man allegedly pulled a handgun and bound both men with rope, said Sgt. Roger 
Ferguson of LAPD's West Valley Division.  
</P>
<P>
 One of the victims managed to free himself and got a handgun of his own. A 
shootout ensued, leaving both victims with chest wounds, Ferguson said.  
</P>
<P>
 Police believe at least one shot hit the suspect as he ran from the house. The 
computer, which police believe the intruder intended to steal, was not taken, 
Ferguson said. 
</P>
<P>
 The two victims were listed in critical condition at Northridge Hospital 
Medical Center.  
</P>
<P>
 A woman also was in the house during the attempted holdup, but was not 
injured, police said. JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
</TEXT>
