<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN TAKES FATAL FALL FROM YARD TO CHANNEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The body of a 40-year-old man who apparently tripped and fell 12 feet from a 
back yard into a concrete flood control channel was found early Saturday 
morning in Tujunga, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Firefighters recovered the body at the bottom of Haines Canyon channel in the 
10000 block of Marcus Avenue after a friend of the man's called police, said 
Bob Collis of the Los Angeles Fire Department. 
</P>
<P>
 "He was in the back yard, tripped and hit his head. He drowned in about 6 
inches of water," said Sgt. Dan Honey of the Los Angeles Police Department's 
Foothill Division. 
</P>
<P>
 The man apparently tripped over a low fence that separates the channel from 
houses, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim's name was not released. JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
