<P>
MAN CRASHES CAR, KILLING SON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A driver who was speeding in the rain crashed his car into a power pole 
Saturday, killing his 29-year-old son, a passenger in the vehicle, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim died at the scene, said Capt. Bob Hancock of the Los Angeles County 
Fire Department.His name was withheld until other relatives could be notified. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver, a 62-year-old Palmdale man, suffered a broken neck in the accident 
and was in critical but stable condition at Antelope Valley Medical Center, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred about 1 p.m. when the driver lost control of the car as 
he headed west on Palmdale Boulevard near 190th Street East. A 32-year-old 
woman, also a passenger, was not seriously injured, said California Highway 
Patrol Officer Bruce Ferrier. 
</P>
<P>
 The impact of the car "sheared the telephone pole off at the bottom and 
knocked it 10 feet back," Hancock said. JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
